TESTING:

error: "command jest not found"

solution: add script:{ "test" : "jest" }
	  run < npm test >
	  --- This solved the issue for me.
	  
	  ------------OR-----------------
	  use npx:
	  < npx jest >
	  
---------- objectContaining v/s object -------------
former is used if you want to check wheteher a specific property is present in the object, you don't care about other properties.
WHEREAS
later is used if you want to check whether the result is of the exact structure.
